.TH "mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm" 9 "mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm \- main routine for sending tm requests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm
.BI "(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc "  ","
.BI "u16 handle "  ","
.BI "uint channel "  ","
.BI "uint id "  ","
.BI "u64 lun "  ","
.BI "u8 type "  ","
.BI "u16 smid_task "  ","
.BI "u16 msix_task "  ","
.BI "u8 timeout "  ","
.BI "u8 tr_method "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ioc" 12
per adapter struct
.IP "handle" 12
device handle
.IP "channel" 12
the channel assigned by the OS
.IP "id" 12
the id assigned by the OS
.IP "lun" 12
lun number
.IP "type" 12
MPI2_SCSITASKMGMT_TASKTYPE__XXX (defined in mpi2_init.h)
.IP "smid_task" 12
smid assigned to the task
.IP "msix_task" 12
MSIX table index supplied by the OS
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout in seconds
.IP "tr_method" 12
Target Reset Method
.SH "CONTEXT"
user
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A generic API for sending task management requests to firmware.

The callback index is set inside `ioc->tm_cb_idx`.
The caller is responsible to check for outstanding commands.
.SH "RETURN"
SUCCESS or FAILED.
